    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-18T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="955"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d955">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 E.W./10–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-18T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 18, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178.<note n="68" xml:id="d955fn68">See telegram 177, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra.</hi>
                    </note> “I am instructed by the Secretary of State to inform you that (1) The
                    American Government has carefully studied the Irish Government’s <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> dated October 9, 1944<note n="69"
                        xml:id="d955fn69">See telegram 165, October 9, from Dublin, <ref
                            target="#pg_1438">p. 1438</ref>.</note> in reply to the request of the
                    American Government for assurances as to Axis war criminals embodied in our <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> dated September 21, 1944;<note n="70"
                        xml:id="d955fn70">See telegram 175, September 16, to Dublin, <ref
                            target="#pg_1426">p. 1426</ref>.</note> (2) The American Government
                    notes that the Irish Government does not vouchsafe the assurances requested and
                    regrets that the Irish Government does not choose to exercise its sovereignty in
                    unequivocal and sympathetic cooperation with the United Nations in proclaiming
                    denial of asylum to Axis war criminals responsible for the horrors that have
                    shocked the civilized world.”</p>
                <p>Repeated to London as No. 58.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
